main event: Chunks of unidentified ice fell from the sky in various areas of Britain, raising concerns and speculation about their origin.
interesting points: The ice chunks coincided with rumors of flying saucers in the UK., One chunk reportedly killed a sheep., Definite reports on 10 cases of ice bombings were collected by the air ministry., Experts suggested the ice could be a result of weather phenomena, but some believe it may originate from space., A five-pound block of ice smashed through a house roof, with no planes present at the time.
witness description: Reports from the British air ministry and various residents who experienced the incidents.
